Paper: hep-th/9407175

Date: 1994-07-26

Title: Four Dimensional Yang - Mills Theory in Local Gauge Invariant Variables

Authors: F.A.Lunev

Comments: 13 pages, MSU-PHYS-HEP-Lu1/94

Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A9 (1994) 2281-2292

It is presented the general method that allows to formulate 4D $SU(N)$ Yang -Mills theory in terms of only local gauge invariant variables. For the caseN=2, that is discussed in details, this gauge invariant formulation appears tobe very similar to $ R^2 $-gravity.